personalInfo.clubAffl: Cedar Creek G&CC (Buena Vista, Georgia), Pinetree CC (Kennesaw, Georgia)

tourBios.carHigh: 2013: Competed on Open Golf Atlanta, a mini-tour in the Atlanta area. Was the leading money-winner, with four victories to his credit. Was also chosen as that circuit's Player of the Year.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Played collegiately at Kennesaw State University, where he won all-region and All-Atlantic Sun Conference honors in his career...Was a member of Kennesaw State's first team to qualify for the NCAA Division I Championship (2011)...Qualified for the 2009 U.S. Open at Bethpage State Park.
tourBios.personal: Some of his favorite golf memories are playing with family, friends and college teammates as well as qualifying for the 2009 U.S. Open...Favorite teams include the Pittsburgh Pirates and the Pittsburgh Steelers, as well as the Kennesaw State Owls...Enjoys "SportsCenter" and "Golf Central."...His favorite athletes in another sport are Roger Federer and Kobe Bryant...Two of his favorite movies are "Caddyshack" and "Happy Gilmore."...The list of golf courses he'd like to play include Augusta National GC, Pebble Beach GL, St. Andrews, Pine Valley GC, Oakmont CC and Cypress Point...Biggest thrill in golf is making birdies and eagles...Says if he weren't playing golf he'd enjoy teaching the game...Enjoys reading any golf book...Would love to trade places with "The Most Interesting Man in the World."...Dream foursome would include his dad, Tiger Woods and his brother...Is a good bowler...His bucket list includes playing as many beautiful golf courses as possible all over the world...Favorite foods include steak, breakfast and Japanese cuisine...Enjoys 1990s rock and roll.
